### Description

Create a new job plan in the specified resource scope (business or business set), based on an **existing** job template.

Prerequisites: the job template exists; the caller has permission to view that template and create job plans in the scope. Plan names must be unique within the same resource scope and job template.

### Request Parameters

#### Body Parameters

| Field           | Type    | Required | Description |
|-----------------|---------|----------|-------------|
| bk_scope_type   | string  | Yes      | Resource scope type. Allowed values: `biz` (business), `biz_set` (business set) |
| bk_scope_id     | string  | Yes      | Resource scope ID matching `bk_scope_type` (business ID or business set ID) |
| job_template_id | long    | Yes      | Job template ID; must be greater than 0; the template must exist |
| name            | string  | Yes      | Job plan name, 1–60 characters; must not contain HTML special characters `<`, `>`, `"`, `'`; must be unique within the same resource scope and job template |
| enable_steps    | array   | No       | Template step IDs to enable in the new plan; if omitted, all template steps are enabled; an empty array is not allowed; every ID must belong to the template |
| variables       | array   | No       | Overrides for template global variables, matched by variable name; fails if the name is unknown or the value type does not match the template; variable names must be unique in one request |

##### variables[] element

| Field           | Type    | Required | Description |
|-----------------|---------|----------|-------------|
| name            | string  | Yes      | Global variable name in the template, matched by name (not by variable ID); must be non-blank |
| value           | string  | No       | Default variable value for string, namespace, ciphertext, associative array, or index array types in the template; ignored when `follow_template` is `true` |
| execute_target  | object  | No       | Execute targets; only when the template variable is an execute-target list and `follow_template` is `false`; must not be used together with `value` |
| follow_template | boolean | No       | Whether to keep the template default. Allowed values: `true` (use template default), `false` (use `value` or `execute_target` from this request; default `false`). When `true`, `execute_target` must not be provided |

##### execute_target

| Field                | Type  | Required | Description |
|----------------------|-------|----------|-------------|
| host_list            | array | No       | Static host list |
| dynamic_group_list   | array | No       | Dynamic group list |
| topo_node_list       | array | No       | CMDB topology node list |

When `execute_target` is provided, at least one of `host_list`, `dynamic_group_list`, and `topo_node_list` must be non-empty.

##### host_list[] element

| Field       | Type   | Required | Description |
|-------------|--------|----------|-------------|
| bk_host_id  | long   | No       | Host ID in CMDB. Either this or `bk_cloud_id` + `ip` is required; if both are set, `bk_host_id` takes precedence |
| bk_cloud_id | long   | No       | Cloud area ID; must be used together with `ip` |
| ip          | string | No       | Host IP; must be used together with `bk_cloud_id` |

##### dynamic_group_list[] element

| Field | Type   | Required | Description |
|-------|--------|----------|-------------|
| id    | string | Yes      | Dynamic group ID |

##### topo_node_list[] element

| Field      | Type   | Required | Description |
|------------|--------|----------|-------------|
| id         | long   | Yes      | Topology node ID |
| node_type  | string | Yes      | Topology node type. Allowed values: `module`, `set` |

### Request Example

- POST

```json
{
    "bk_scope_type": "biz",
    "bk_scope_id": "2",
    "job_template_id": 1000,
    "name": "my-api-plan",
    "enable_steps": [101, 102, 103],
    "variables": [
        {
            "name": "TARGET_DIR",
            "value": "/data/release",
            "follow_template": false
        },
        {
            "name": "KEEP_TEMPLATE_DEFAULT",
            "follow_template": true
        },
        {
            "name": "HOST_TARGET",
            "follow_template": false,
            "execute_target": {
                "host_list": [
                    {
                        "bk_host_id": 10001
                    },
                    {
                        "bk_cloud_id": 0,
                        "ip": "127.0.0.2"
                    }
                ],
                "dynamic_group_list": [
                    {
                        "id": "asdo8gojhasdfskft7pr5"
                    }
                ],
                "topo_node_list": [
                    {
                        "id": 1000,
                        "node_type": "module"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

